[41:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'re a connoisseur, they\'re all going to taste like what they are, a sweet tomato slurry. So, how do you make the choice? Some people might go for the cheapest option. Other people might go for the most expensive option. Some people might only purchase ketchup that contains real sugar as opposed to'

[41:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'high-fructose corn syrup. But an overwhelming majority of people will make the choice based on brand. They\'re going to grab the Heinz because it\'s what they know. Heinz does not make the tastiest ketchup, the cheapest ketchup, or the'

[41:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'healthiest ketchup, but 70% of all ketchup sold in the United States and over half of ketchup sold globally is produced by Heinz. That is the power of brand. Even in an industry as competitive and saturated as'

[42:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'condiments and in a sea of identical products, Heinz brand has given them an effective monopoly on the single most widely consumed condiment in the world. And as business owners, we should all aspire to become monopolies.'

[42:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now we have to ask the question, what does brand mean for OnlyFans models specifically? The easiest way to define brand in the context of OnlyFans is a combination of three qualities: recognizability, association, and'

[42:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'audience identity. Recognizability is simply how quickly can I recognize the creator? When I say the words Coca-Cola, it literally conjures the image of the Coca-Cola logo in your head. You can\'t help but think'

[42:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of it. Red label, white cursive, maybe you think of your favorite Coke product. That is not an accident. Coca-Cola has spent the last 134 years blasting that logo on every surface they can, from cans and bottles to sports jerseys and'

[42:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'TV screens, with the explicit goal of ensuring that the word Coca-Cola is etched into your soul. For OnlyFans creators, we don\'t have 100 years to establish our brand, but we need to approach with the same principles in mind. What visual or auditory cues can we use to enhance recognition of our'

[43:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'brand? How do we make it so that the microsecond our audience sees one of our reels, they know it\'s our creator and they stop in their tracks? Association is the next layer. Recognition is necessary but'

[43:17] [scene:talk]
